    <div class="intro" id="faq">
        <div>
            <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">Is Givingly a non-profit organization?</p>
            <p class="answer">Yes - Givingly is a non-profit organization based in Toronto. Our mission is to connect non-profit organizations and charities who need help in solving a problem, with professionals who have the right skills.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">Why should I volunteer?</p>
            <p class="answer">If you are a professional, your expertise and experiences are highly sought after by the non-profit organizations serving our community. It is rewarding to make a difference with something you do so well, in our opinion! Also, volunteering is a great way to build your network and add projects to your resume and portfolio.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">What's the commitment level to volunteer?</p>
            <p class="answer">Everything posted on our marketplace is a project - we ensure that they have clear goals and deliverables, and that they are not open-ended volunteer positions. Because of this, the commitment level will vary by project, but they are very transparent, and you have control over them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">Do I get recognized for volunteering?</p>
            <p class="answer">Yes - Givingly keeps track of all the projects you have volunteered on along with the hours you spent volunteering, which we will make available to you in your profile. We are working on ways and partnering with organizations to let you redeem those hours for rewarding experiences.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">How are the projects vetted?</p>
            <p class="answer">Before any project is posted on Givingly, we work extensively with the non-profit organization to scope and structure the project. This is to make sure that the project creates lasting impact for the organization and is meaningful for the volunteers. This takes time, but we do this to ensure a great experience for both our non-profits and the professionals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">Does it cost money?</p>
            <p class="answer">For professionals, Givingly is completely free. For non-profit organizations, posting your project is completely free and we only charge a fee when you have found a professional. This fee is used to pay for the cost of providing the platform.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="q">
            <p class="question">How do I get involved?</p>
            <p class="answer">Givingy is currently in beta - meaning that we are testing our platform with a small group of users to ensure that the it is easy to use. If you are interested in joining, please leave your email in the form below, and we will send you an invite as soon as we can!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ui divider"></div>
    <div class="join">
        <h2>Can't wait to get started?</h2>
        <p>Givingly is currently in private beta. Leave your email and we'll send you an invite soon! We promise we won't share your info with anyone or spam your inbox.</p>
        <div class="ui form segment">
            <div class="mand"><%= fa_icon 'asterisk' %>Indicates required fields</div>
            <%= form_tag subscribe_path(@list_id), method: 'POST', class: "subscription_form" do %>
            <div class="field">
                <%= label_tag 'email' do %>
                Email<%= fa_icon 'asterisk' %>
                <% end %>
                <%= text_field_tag 'email',nil, maxlength:'250' %>
            </div>        
            <div class="i_am_a grouped inline fields">
